# Development Workflow Guidelines

## Context
- Defines the standard development workflow
- Provides command references for common tasks
- Ensures consistent development practices

## Requirements
- Use UV for all package management (never pip or poetry)
- Run all commands through Makefile when available
- Follow feature branch workflow (branch from develop)
- Write tests before or alongside new features
- Run linters before committing code
- Update documentation for new features
- Use semantic commit messages
- Ensure all tests pass before pushing

## Common Commands
```bash
# Environment Setup
make setup           # Initial project setup
make python          # Install Python with UV

# Development
make run            # Run locally with Uvicorn
make run-dev        # Run with Gunicorn (dev)
make run-prod       # Run with Gunicorn (prod)

# Testing
make test           # Run all tests
make test-cov       # Run tests with coverage

# Code Quality
make lint           # Run pre-commit hooks
make clean-cache    # Clean Python cache

# Docker
make build          # Build Docker image
make up             # Start containers
make down           # Stop containers
make logs           # View container logs

# Database
uv run alembic upgrade head        # Apply migrations
uv run alembic revision -m "msg"   # Create migration
```

## Examples
<example>
# Good: Complete feature workflow
# 1. Create feature branch
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git checkout -b feature/add-user-roles

# 2. Install dependencies if needed
uv add some-package

# 3. Create database migration
uv run alembic revision -m "add roles to users table"

# 4. Implement feature with tests
# - Create/update models
# - Add repository methods
# - Implement service logic
# - Add API endpoints
# - Write comprehensive tests

# 5. Run tests and linters
make test
make lint

# 6. Commit with semantic message
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add user roles management

- Add roles column to users table
- Implement role-based access control
- Add endpoints for role management
- Include comprehensive test coverage"

# 7. Push and create PR
git push origin feature/add-user-roles
</example>

<example type="invalid">
# Invalid: Poor workflow practices
# Wrong: Using pip instead of uv
pip install fastapi

# Wrong: Committing directly to main
git checkout main
git add .
git commit -m "fixed stuff"  # Wrong: Non-descriptive message

# Wrong: No testing
git push origin main  # Wrong: Pushing without tests

# Wrong: Not using Makefile commands
python main.py  # Wrong: Use 'make run' instead
docker-compose up  # Wrong: Use 'make up' instead
</example>